    </refmeta>

    <refnamediv>
        <refname>j4status</refname>
        <refpurpose>status line generator</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>

    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <cmdsynopsis>
            <command>j4status</command>
            <arg choice="opt">-o <replaceable class="parameter">plugin</replaceable></arg>
            <arg choice="opt" rep="repeat">-i <replaceable class="parameter">plugin</replaceable></arg>
        </cmdsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>

    <refsect1>
        <title>Description</title>

        <para>
            j4status is a status line generator to track remote or local events and do actions the user wants to.
        </para>
        <para>
            j4status is composed by a core, the application itself, and various plugins.
            Plugins may be output plugins or input plugins.
        </para>
        <para>Two official output plugins are distributed with j4status:</para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><command>flat</command></term>
                <listitem><para>which displays flat text</para></listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><command>i3bar</command></term>
                <listitem><para>which implements the <ulink url="http://i3wm.org/docs/i3bar-protocol.html">i3bar JSON protocol</ulink></para></listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
        <para>Four official input plugins are distributed with j4status:</para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><command>time</command> (see <citerefentry><refentrytitle>j4status-time.conf</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry>)</term>
                <listitem><para>a plugin to display date and time</para></listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><command>file-monitor</command> (see <citerefentry><refentrytitle>j4status-file-monitor.conf</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry>)</term>
                <listitem><para>a plugin to monitor files and dispaly their content</para></listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><command>nm</command> (see <citerefentry><refentrytitle>j4status-nm.conf</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry>)</term>
                <listitem><para>a NetworkManager client plugin, to display network status</para></listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><command>upower</command></term>
                <listitem><para>a UPower client plugin, to display battery status</para></listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsect1>

    <refsect1>
        <title>Options</title>

        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><option>-o</option></term>
                <term><option>--output=<replaceable class="parameter">plugin</replaceable></option></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Specify the output plugin</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

            <varlistentry>
                <term><option>-i</option></term>
                <term><option>--input=<replaceable class="parameter">plugin</replaceable></option></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Specify an input plugin</para>
                    <para>May be specified multiple times.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

            <varlistentry>
                <term><option>-V</option></term>
                <term><option>--version</option></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Print version</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

            <varlistentry>
                <term><option>-h</option></term>
                <term><option>--help</option></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Show help options</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsect1>

    <refsect1>
        <title>Examples</title>

        <example>
            <title>Drop-in replacement for a notification daemon</title>

            <para>
                With its <command>dbus</command> and <command>nd</command> plugins, eventd can be a drop-in replacement for a notification daemon.
            </para>

            <para>
                To use this feature, just add the following line to your <filename>~/.xsession</filename> or equivalent file:
            </para>
            <programlisting>eventdctl --auto-spawn notification-daemon ${DISPLAY}</programlisting>
            <para>
                See <citerefentry><refentrytitle>eventdctl</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> for <command>eventdctl</command> call precisions.
            </para>
        </example>
    </refsect1>

    <refsect1>
        <title>Environment</title>

        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><varname>$J4STATUS_PLUGINS_DIR</varname></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Additional directory to browse for plugins.</para>
                    <para>This directory is browsed first, before standard directories.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

            <varlistentry>
                <term><varname>$J4STATUS_CONFIG_FILE</varname></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Additional configuration file to check.</para>
                    <para>This file is checked first, before standard files, to override them.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsect1>

    <refsect1>
        <title>Sockets</title>

        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><filename><varname>$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR</varname>/&PACKAGE_NAME;/private</filename></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Used internally by <citerefentry><refentrytitle>eventdctl</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> to communicate with eventd. This location can be overridden by the <option>--private-socket</option> option.</para>
                    <para>If <varname>$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR</varname> is not set, we use <varname>$XDG_CACHE_HOME</varname>, with a fallback to <filename>~/.cache</filename>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsect1>

    <refsect1>
